proto

Class FileMC

  • java.lang.Object
    • proto.FileMC

  • public class FileMC
extends Object
    Write data structures in sequential order using Google's Prototype Buffer. The same class can be used to read data from ntuples. Each data record inside files is compressed on-fly using zip. A protocol Buffers file is provided which can be used for C++ input. Use the CBook package to create such files in C++.

    Author:
    S.Chekanov

    • Constructor Detail

      • FileMC

        public FileMC(String file,
      String option)
        Open a file to write/read objects to/from a file in sequential order. If "w" option is set, the old file will be removed. Use close() to flash the buffer and close the file.
        Parameters:
        file - File name
        option - Option to create the file. If "w" - write a file (or read) file, if "r" only read created file.
